{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"CSS Box Model","slug":"css-box-model","subject":"CSS","category":"Web Development","level":"Beginner","estimated_read_time":"12 mins","prerequisites":["CSS Margins","CSS Padding","CSS Borders"],"learning_objectives":["Understand the Box Model concept","Identify the 4 parts: Content, Padding, Border, Margin","Calculate the total width and height of an element","Learn about box-sizing: border-box"],"theory":"All HTML elements can be considered as boxes. The CSS Box Model is essentially a box that wraps around every HTML element. It consists of: \n\n1.  **Content**: The actual content of the box, where text and images appear.\n2.  **Padding**: Clears an area around the content. The padding is transparent.\n3.  **Border**: A border that goes around the padding and content.\n4.  **Margin**: Clears an area outside the border. The margin is transparent.\n\nTotal Width = width + left padding + right padding + left border + right border + left margin + right margin.","syntax":"div {\n  width: 300px;\n  padding: 10px;\n  border: 5px solid gray;\n  margin: 10px;\n}","examples":[{"code":".box {\n  width: 320px;\n  padding: 10px;\n  border: 5px solid gray;\n  margin: 0;\n}","output":"Actual rendered width = 320px + 20px (padding) + 10px (border) = 350px.","explanation":"By default, CSS adds padding and border TO the specified width."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Not accounting for border and padding in width","correction":"This breaks layouts. Use `box-sizing: border-box` to include padding/border in the width calculation.","example":"* { box-sizing: border-box; }"}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"What is the difference between `content-box` and `border-box`?","answer":"In `content-box` (default), width only includes content. In `border-box`, width includes content + padding + border.","difficulty":"Important"},{"question":"If width is 100px, padding is 20px, border is 5px. What is total width in standard CSS?","answer":"100 + 20*2 + 5*2 = 150px.","difficulty":"Easy"}],"practice_problems":[{"problem":"Calculate the total height: height: 100px, padding-top: 20px, border-bottom: 5px.","hint":"Sum vertical values.","solution":"100 + 20 + 5 = 125px","difficulty":"Medium"}],"real_world_use_cases":[{"scenario":"Global Reset","description":"Most modern websites apply `* { box-sizing: border-box; }` at the very start to make sizing intuitive.","code":"/* The first rule in most projects */\n*, *::before, *::after {\n  box-sizing: border-box;\n}"}],"exam_notes":["Margin is the outermost layer.","Background color usually covers Content and Padding regions."],"summary":"The Box Model is the foundation of layout. Understanding it is critical for anyone working with CSS.","order":12},"courseTutorials":[{"slug":"css-introduction","path":"content/css/css-introduction.json","title":"Introduction to CSS","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":1},{"slug":"css-syntax","path":"content/css/css-syntax.json","title":"CSS Syntax","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":2},{"slug":"css-best-practices","path":"content/css/css-best-practices.json","title":"CSS Best Practices","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":3},{"slug":"css-borders","path":"content/css/css-borders.json","title":"CSS Borders","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":4},{"slug":"css-colors","path":"content/css/css-colors.json","title":"CSS Colors","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":5},{"slug":"css-backgrounds","path":"content/css/css-backgrounds.json","title":"CSS Backgrounds","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":6},{"slug":"css-comments","path":"content/css/css-comments.json","title":"CSS Comments","category":"Web Development","subject":"CSS","description":"","order":7},{"slug":"css-interview","path":"content/css/css-interview.json","title":"CSS Interview Preparation